The paper deals with the design of forward error correction codes for communication systems, specifically for hybrid automatic repeat request (HARQ) protocols and adaptive modulation and coding. This falls under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the use of set-partitioned QAM constellations, which falls under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). The algorithms proposed for designing throughput-maximizing codes involve optimization techniques, which falls under the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the practical implementation of the proposed codes, which falls under the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
